    "Imai et al. (2021) proposed a method to generate many scenario earthquake shaking maps from existing shaking maps using modal decomposition of proper orthogonal decomposition and an empirical copula.",
    "The quality assessment and selection of groundmotion records are necessary to improve the groundmotion prediction model.",
    "Dupuis et al. (2023) applied a supervised DL-based model to this issue.",
    "Their model can estimate the quality and minimum usable frequency for each record component.",
    "It can handle one-, two-, or three-component records, providing flexibility to assess record quality based on various requirements."
